messages.content: You are tasked with creating a structured output from the provided user message.

Full HTTP request path:
- /request/register

All HTTP methods acceptable:
- false

HTTP method support (based on the code):
- HEAD: false
- POST: true
- OPTIONS: false
- TRACE: false
- GET: false
- PUT: false
- DELETE: false
- PATCH: false

Explanation:
- The controller class has no class-level @RequestMapping, so method-level mappings are full paths as written.
- The registerRequest method is annotated with @RequestMapping(value = "/request/register", method = RequestMethod.POST), so only POST is explicitly mapped for the /request/register endpoint.
- No mapping for HEAD, GET, PUT, DELETE, PATCH, OPTIONS or TRACE appears in the code for this endpoint, and the requirement was to base acceptability on the code (not on implicit/container behaviors), so those methods are reported as not acceptable.
- "All methods" is false because the code maps only POST for this path.
